":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSuwrN","text_ar":"نُصُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may also be a pl. of the same, as occurring in the verse of Khidásh, cited above: (M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaASiyru","text_ar":"اَنَاصِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. pl., being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoSaArN","text_ar":"اَنْصَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorN","text_ar":"نَصْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as sing. and pl., (M, K,) being an inf. n. employed as an epithet, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anoSaAru","text_ar":"الاَنْصَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Assistants of the Prophet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) of [the tribes of] El-Ows and El-Khazraj; (TA;) being an epithet applied to them especially, (M, K,) and used as a subst., as though it were the name of a tribe, wherefore the rel. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoSaAriY~N","text_ar":"اَنْصَارِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is used as sing.] is formed from it. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["Sgh","K","S","M","A","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}